abstract: A decade after the financial crisis, multiple Federal Reserve rate increases are at last making it possible to earn a decent yield with little risk.
snippet: A decade after the financial crisis, multiple Federal Reserve rate increases are at last making it possible to earn a decent yield with little risk.
lead_paragraph: For the first time since the financial crisis, playing it safe is paying off for income investors.

abstract: The subway’s leader, Andy Byford, says he needs $40 billion to fix the system. Congestion pricing could help pay for his plan, but it won’t cover the entire tab.
snippet: The subway’s leader, Andy Byford, says he needs $40 billion to fix the system. Congestion pricing could help pay for his plan, but it won’t cover the entire tab.
lead_paragraph: The idea of charging drivers to enter Manhattan’s busiest neighborhoods has been debated for decades, but it could finally have a real shot in Albany next year.

abstract: The Las Vegas couple, who had already given $55 million, delivered a last-minute infusion of cash to help the party remain in control in Washington.
snippet: The Las Vegas couple, who had already given $55 million, delivered a last-minute infusion of cash to help the party remain in control in Washington.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Sheldon and Miriam Adelson, the Las Vegas Republicans who have already spent more money on federal races this year than any other donors in either political party, are piling even more of their casino fortune into Republicans’ campaign efforts, people with knowledge of their plans said Thursday.

headline_main: New York Today: How to Register to Vote

abstract: Party leaders are building a firewall around a few dozen purple districts, and cutting off lawmakers who appear unable to win.
snippet: Party leaders are building a firewall around a few dozen purple districts, and cutting off lawmakers who appear unable to win.
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — Vice President Mike Pence laid out a hopeful vision for the midterm elections this week as he campaigned for Representative Pete Sessions of Texas, telling Republican donors that candidates like Mr. Sessions could stop Democrats from winning the House in November.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has rejoined the party he abandoned to launch his political career in 2001, when he became the Republican mayor of New York City.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has rejoined the party he abandoned to launch his political career in 2001, when he became the Republican mayor of New York City.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg, the Democrat-turned-Republican-turned-independent, says he is returning to his roots: He has re-registered as a Democrat — an initial but essential step toward a possible run for president in 2020 as a Democrat.
